ZH: 我经常去找一位占卜师预测我的未来。
EN: I often go to a fortune teller to predict my future.

ZH: 她通过占卜揭示了一些他不知道的事情。
EN: She revealed some things he didn't know through divination.

ZH: 我妈妈每天都要查看她的占卜星座。
EN: My mom checks her horoscope for divination every day.

ZH: 占卜存在已有数千年的历史。
EN: Divination has a history of thousands of years.

ZH: 她给我占卜后告诉我提防某个人。
EN: She told me to watch out for someone after divining for me.

ZH: 占卜算是一门神秘的艺术。
EN: Divination is considered a mysterious art.

ZH: 我曾尝试过一些简单的占卜方式，但不太准确。
EN: I have tried some simple divination methods, but they are not very accurate.

ZH: 占卜可以帮助我们做出正确的决策。
EN: Divination can help us make the right decisions.

ZH: 他相信占卜是一种与神灵对话的方式。
EN: He believes that divination is a way of communicating with the gods.

ZH: 她研究不同种类的占卜术已经有十年之久。
EN: She has been studying different types of divination for ten years.

ZH: 占卜师通过摇晃铜钱来展示命运。
EN: The fortune teller demonstrates fate by shaking copper coins.

ZH: 他利用塔罗牌进行占卜并给出建议。
EN: He uses tarot cards for divination and gives advice.

ZH: 占卜并不能完全预测未来，但可以提供一些指引。
EN: Divination cannot predict the future completely, but it can provide some guidance.

ZH: 我会去占卜师那里咨询一下关于我工作的问题。
EN: I will consult a fortune teller about my job-related questions.

ZH: 许多人渴望知道占卜的准确性。
EN: Many people are eager to know the accuracy of divination.

ZH: 占卜也可以在一些特殊的场合使用，如结婚仪式。
EN: Divination can also be used in some special occasions, such as wedding ceremonies.

ZH: 我曾尝试过通过签文占卜来获得一些讯息。
EN: I have tried using oracle bone inscriptions to obtain some information through divination.

ZH: 不同文化中存在着各种各样的占卜方式。
EN: There are various divination methods in different cultures.

ZH: 她通过占卜预言了我即将发生的事情。
EN: She predicted what would happen to me through divination.

ZH: 我觉得占卜有时候是准确的，有时候则是靠运气。
EN: I think divination is sometimes accurate, and sometimes it depends on luck.
